      <originalsloc id="aspace_ea069f700b26ecf656ab52c987d4edb2">
         <head>Existence and Location of Originals</head>
         <p>the entire collection is available on microfilm (HM 264) and in the British East India Company Records (MS 925).   The collection consists of reports of agents of the East India Company in Mahi Kantha in Gujarat (western India) and dispatches from East India officials in Bombay sent to London. The reports provide a history of the Mahi Kantha before 1821 and describe political events there through 1839. The documents are all copies.</p>  
